1. input.jsx [ type, name, id , class]

Explantion

these attributes are added in input state you can change these attributes
 by changing the object of input having fields Type of input
  Name represent the Name i-e FirstName or last name 
class is use to customize the input through our own css 

2. button.jsx[type, name, id , class,value,text]

Explantion

these attributes are added in input state you can change these attributes
 by changing the object of button having fields Type of button
  Name: represent the Name i-e btn-submit 
class: is use to customize the button through our own css 
Value : initally the is assigned the state '' later we will setstate i-e update the state onclickEvent


3. label.jsx [  class ,text, for ] 

class: is use to customize the label through our own css 
text: is use to assign the label Name i-e FirstName or LastName or Address etc
for : label for

4. select.jsx [ , name, id , class,placeholder,countryOptions[]]

placeholder: represents the default value of select i-e select any 
countryOptions[]: an array of country option which will populate the values of select 

5 textarea.jsx [  name,type, id , class cols,rows,placeholder]

cols: representS numbers of rows of textarea
rows: represents the numbers of cols of textarea